SUMMARY:Vivian Lu & Rose Tianyu Qi: Don’t Look At Me
LOCATION:ARC Gallery\, 1463 W Chicago Ave\, Chicago\, IL 60642
DESCRIPTION:Don’t Look At Me is an interactive installation in which a 
 life-cast wax sculpture is progressively destroyed by the attention of i
 ts viewers. When a viewer looks at the body\, the observed area will be 
 melted. The wax softens\, deforms\, and melts away. The sculpture does n
 ot reset...\nMore info: https://thevisualist.org/2026/05/vivian-lu-rose-
 tianyu-qi-dont-look-at-me/\nVenue site: https://www.arcgallery.org/exhib
 itions-archive/vivian-lu-rose-qi
